From 2222222222222222222222222222222222222222 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ASRock Rack <noreply@asrock.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] system: don't error-log the optional bios_active lookup

System::version() best-effort propagates the SMBIOS BIOS version to
/xyz/openbmc_project/software/bios_active (Software.Version). That object only
exists on boards whose BIOS is tracked under the legacy path; on boards using
the newer code-update design the BIOS is a HostSPIFlash software object and
bios_active does not exist. getService() is used ONLY for this optional lookup,
so demote its "object not found" mapper failure from error to debug (and fix the
swapped SERVICE/PATH log labels). The BIOS version remains available on the
smbios System object regardless.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [board-specific log-noise reduction]
---
 src/system.cpp | 13 +++++++++----
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/src/system.cpp
+++ b/src/system.cpp
@@ -90,10 +90,15 @@
     }
     catch (const sdbusplus::exception_t& e)
     {
-        lg2::error("Error in mapper method call - {ERROR}, SERVICE - "
-                   "{SERVICE}, PATH - {PATH}",
-                   "ERROR", e.what(), "SERVICE", objectPath.c_str(), "PATH",
-                   interface.c_str());
+        // getService() is only used for the optional BIOS-version propagation
+        // to /xyz/openbmc_project/software/bios_active. On boards using the
+        // newer code-update design (the BIOS is a HostSPIFlash software object)
+        // that legacy path does not exist, so a "not found" here is an expected
+        // condition, not an error worth logging at error level.
+        lg2::debug("Mapper lookup skipped (object absent) - {ERROR}, PATH - "
+                   "{PATH}, INTERFACE - {INTERFACE}",
+                   "ERROR", e.what(), "PATH", objectPath.c_str(), "INTERFACE",
+                   interface.c_str());

         return std::string{};
     }
